ANTHRAX, HUMAN - KYRGYZSTAN (10): REVIEW
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 19 Sep 2008
Source: IA AkiPress, [trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://kg.akipress.org/news/61622>


Since May 2008, the epizootic and epidemiological situation with
anthrax in Kyrgyzstan has become extremely bad.

According to data from the Ministry of Health, since 15 Sep 2008, 42
cases of anthrax have been recorded:

Jalal-Abad/Zhakalabad region: - 21 (Nookensky district - 15, Suzaksky
district - 6);
Osh region - 8 (Uzgensky district - 3, Aravansky district - 3, and in
the town of Osh - 2);
Batken region - 6 (Kadamzhaysky district);
Chuysk region - 5 (Zhayilsky district);
Talass region - 2 (Karabuurinsky district).

The cutaneous form of anthrax was confirmed in all patients. Medical
preventive measures were carried out in all foci of infection.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[While Kyrgyzstan suffers from severe infrastructure problems, in its
bureaucracies, it does take anthrax seriously. But mobilizing
cost-effective proactive vaccination programs in the areas of highest
risk is proving to be a real challenge. To add some scale to the 2008
numbers, in all of 2000, they reported 2 human cases, 2001 (4), 2002
(8), 2003 (20), 2004 (31), 2005 (28), and in 2006 (41). I suspect
that part of the annual increase reflects improved reporting.

For Kyrgyzstan, go to:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_pol_05.jpg>. - Mod.MHJ]
